OL,3,CCrunch time for carrots and potatoes
OL,4,Cas dry conditions jeopardise harvest
OL,6,FBut there's a snag - it hasn't rained.
OL,8,F"Peas are a disaster," explains John.
OL,9,F"It all started with such promise,
OL,10,Fwith good planting.
OL,12,F"Particularly in Lincolnshire, we just
OL,13,Fhaven't had enough rain. The plants
OL,14,Fhaven't developed."
OL,16,FAt the start of the season, farmers in
OL,17,FLincolnshire were getting about two
OL,18,Ftonnes of peas per acre. By the time
OL,19,Fit was wrapping up, they were getting
OL,20,Fjust 0.1 tonnes per acre, a 95%
OL,21,Fdecrease.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/15
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
